    <a href="#"><img class="thin-orange-border" src="https://i.pinimg.com/originals/ca/11/8c/ca118c1c282c75ad697101beb8cd5096.jpg" alt="a wild dog standing on a rock."></a>
  
    <p>African wild dog, (Lycaon pictus), also called Cape hunting dog, African hunting dog, or hyena dog, wild African carnivore that differs from the rest of the members of the dog family (Canidae) in having only four toes on each foot. Its coat is short, sparse, and irregularly blotched with yellow, black, and white. The African wild dog is about 76–102 cm (30–41 inches) long, exclusive of its 31–41-cm tail, stands about 60 cm (24 inches) tall at the shoulder, and weighs about 16–23 kg (35–50 pounds).</p>
    <div>
    <p>Things wild dogs love:</p>
     <ul>
       <li>running</li>
       <li>hunting</li>
       <li>social grooming</li>
     </ul>
    <p>Top 3 things wild dogs hate:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>loud sounds</li>
      <li>thunder</li>
      <li>other predators</li>
    </ol>
